@MKVGuy
Windows media player (WMP) cannot play mkv files unless a codec pack has been installed. And then it only understands srt format but it cannot turn off the subtitles (it doesn't recognise muxed subtitles).  

VLC on the other hand can enable & disable subtitles whether it is muxed or in srt. I think we should encourage people to use VLC to play mkv and then spread awareness of the option to enable/disable subtitles simply by pressing V on the keyboard. I think you can include this tip in the description/summary of the torrent as well as in the info text file that is included as part of the download.
